##From 20,000 / ton to 400,000 / ton, the price of meltblown fabric, the core material of the mask, has skyrocketed

From 20,000 / ton to 400,000 / ton, in just over a month, the price of face mask "heart" melt-blown cloth has increased nearly 20 times. It is concluded that the main reason for the price increase is the mismatch between the production capacity of meltblown fabric and that of mask

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Wayne Wang, CAIJING correspondent

By Lu Ling | editor

The price of meltblown fabric, the core ingredient known as the "heart" of the mask, soared again, doubling in a matter of days.

CAIJING reporter recently learned that after the price rose to more than 200,000 yuan / ton at the end of February, the price of meltblown cloth has almost doubled to about 400,000 yuan / ton in a few days. Before the outbreak, the market price was only 18,000 yuan per ton. From January 24, the city of Wuhan has been closed, a short period of more than a month, the price of meltblown cloth has risen nearly 20 times.

"Out of stock" , "orders are full" , this is the "financial" reporter to buy identity consulting meltblown cloth suppliers to hear the most replies.

"We have stopped taking orders, and we simply can not supply them, " Liu Feng (not his real name) , a manufacturer of meltblown cloth in Beijing, told Caijing. The price has risen from nearly 20,000 yuan per ton before the outbreak to more than 400,000 yuan per ton now, now "one price a day" , the increase was so large that he did not expect.

Why is melt-blown cloth so in short supply?

"The mismatching between meltblown cloth and mask production capacity is the main reason for the price increase, " senior experts in the industry told CAIJING.

Liu Feng also believes that "supply and demand is this round of meltblown cloth prices soaring one of the key factors. " Before the epidemic, meltblown cloth enough, mask demand led to domestic meltblown cloth production was small. After the outbreak, many enterprises have expanded production, production masks, core materials melt-blown cloth usage surge, production enterprises are difficult to deal with, resulting in a gap. At the same time, the layers of middle prices to sell, hoarding and profiteering, exacerbated the tension between supply and demand.

In addition, with the recent escalation of the international epidemic, the market demand for face masks has continued to increase, and the substantial increase in demand has also led to a continuing shortage of core raw materials.

In addition to the above-mentioned factors, the high cost of equipment and the long period of production line construction and commissioning are considered as the important factors restricting the production capacity of meltblown cloth. In addition, blindly expand production, whether it will lead to the end of the epidemic of overcapacity, but also make some meltblown cloth manufacturers worry, dare not expand production.

Facing the shortage of melt-blown cloth, more than enterprises have added melt-blown cloth production line. Among them, state-owned Sinopec decided on February 24 to invest about 200 million yuan to speed up 10 meltblown cloth production lines, which will increase daily meltblown cloth production capacity by 18 tons. Among them, Beijing Yan Mountains petrochemical will build two meltblown cloth production lines, is expected to start production around March 8.

The industry experts said that after March, melt-blown cloth market supply tension will gradually ease. First, domestic meltblown cloth production capacity continued to increase, and second, overseas imports have been shipped.

Some local governments have also introduced support policies to help link equipment and raw material procurement, fixed-point meltblown cloth production enterprise equipment procurement costs, labor costs to subsidize funds. To co-ordinate loans to meet the liquidity needs of enterprises. To meet the requirements of epidemic prevention materials, the government will be out of pocket procurement, as a strategic reserve.

The surge in demand and higher prices have brought a corresponding response from the capital market. Taida shares (Url) , dawn shares (002838.SZ ) , Xinlong Holdings, Soyut and so many other melt-blown cloth concept shares continue to be popular. Dawn shares in which the cumulative rise of 286.82% far ahead.

The price jumped 20-fold

Meltblown cloth is the main raw material of the filter layer, which is called the "heart" of the mask. Masks generally have three layers of protection, outer, inner and Middle Layers. The inner and outer layers are made of common spunbonded non-woven fabrics in accordance with medical standards, while the middle layer is made of meltblown fabrics, which is the key of filtration protection.

In the huge demand, the price of meltblown cloth is soaring.

"We don't have any in stock at the moment, and our order book is already in June, " Liu said. Another meltblown cloth middleman bid 420,000, in the face of reporters on the "High Price" of the query, its said: "You see, if you do not today, immediately sold to others. "

In a number of meltblown cloth collection wechat group, meltblown cloth in recent days the price has been fried to about 400,000 yuan. A Zhejiang trading company offered 400,000 yuan per ton of BFE99 medical meltblown cloth, 25g / M2, imported from Germany; another seller, shipped from Fujian, offered 430,000 yuan per ton; and another claimed to have 20 tons in stock, the price is 400,000 / ton; some companies insist on "only exchange but not sell" , with one offering 200,000 disposable surgical masks for a ton of medical grade 95 meltzer cloth. Nevertheless, there are still people in the group are looking for the source of meltblown cloth.

On January 28, the People's Daily quoted a source as saying that the market price of the melt blown cloth, a special filter material for masks, was 18,000 yuan per ton, according to a local enterprise.

By this measure, the price of meltblown cloth has risen nearly 20-fold in the more than a month since Wuhan announced its closure on January 24.

Lin Fei (not his real name) , the head of a small mask manufacturer in Dongguan, felt more keenly the boom in meltblown fabric. Before the outbreak, he said, it was usually 20,000 yuan per ton. Around the Spring Festival, it doubled to 40,000 yuan per ton. Then it went all the way up to 200,000-300,000 yuan per ton a week ago, and now it's more than 400,000 yuan per ton. Now it's "one price a day. ". Within a month, it had risen 20-fold, more than he had expected.

The price of raw materials soared, so that some small and medium-sized mask manufacturers face "no rice under the POT" dilemma. "Even if so expensive, still can not buy. " Lin Fei said, now meltblown cloth has "a cloth hard to find, " large mask enterprises have their own government departments to coordinate raw materials, small enterprises are fast "out of food. ".

He used to buy from places like Henan, Hubei and Zhejiang, but now strategic goods like meltblown cloth are prioritized for local use, making them hard for outsiders to buy. "Now you just have to ask acquaintances to buy, " he said, this has also led to a lot of masks on the market idle.

Several domestic manufacturers of meltblown cloth told Caijing that during the outbreak, large-scale production plants were basically controlled by the government, and products were uniformly purchased by the government or sold to designated mask-producing enterprises, which could not be sold to the outside world.

"The factory is guarded by armed police. We have already pushed out all orders from outside customers. The products are mainly sold to local enterprises at a fair price, about 100,000 yuan per ton, which is quite different from the prices on the outside market. The government will give some subsidies, " said a designated manufacturer of meltblown cloth in Shanghai.

It is understood that the domestic production of melt-blown cloth overall presents a small and scattered situation. At present, the domestic meltblown cloth production higher enterprises include Shandong Junfu non-woven Fabric Co. , Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Shandong Junfu) , Tianjin Taida Clean Materials Co. , Ltd. , Xinlong Holding (000955.Sz ) and so on. The daily production capacity of leading enterprises is usually between 7 tons and 15 tons.

Shandong Junfu a staff member in an interview with the "Caijing" reporter, said that the company's mask material meltblown cloth daily output of 15 tons, is the largest meltblown cloth manufacturers. The company currently has 7 meltblown production lines.

Why are raw materials in short supply

Meltblown cloth production capacity and mask production capacity stage mismatch, is considered by industry experts as the main reason for the price increase of meltblown cloth.

Before this outbreak, the domestic meltblown cloth production capacity of Meltblown non-woven fabric is relatively small. In 2018, China's Meltblown non-woven fabric production was about 53,400 tons, with a daily output of about 146 tons, according to data from the China Association of Industrial Textiles. However, the melt-blown cloth is not only used for masks, but also for environmental protection materials, clothing materials, battery separator materials.

"China's meltblown fabric production capacity is not big, if the 2019 production of 6 billion masks, even if it is all N95 masks, the maximum meltblown fabric 20,000 tons (an average of more than 50 tons per day) , " an industry expert told Caijing.

At the same time, with the spread of the global epidemic and the acceleration of the process of domestic enterprises to resume work, the market demand for face masks blowout. Huachuang securities recently based on the need to resume work across the country to do an analysis, pointed out that China's secondary and tertiary employment of a total of 530 million people, such as a mask per person per day need 530 million per day. According to China News Service on February 27, the United States Health Secretary on the issue of the United States Mask Reserve, said that the United States has a gap of 270 million masks.

A huge gap in mask demand and rising production led to the original inventory of melt-blown cloth was consumed in an instant. Based on the production of 90 to 1 million disposable masks per ton of meltblown cloth, the daily production of more than 100 tons can only support the national production of 100 million masks per day under the current epidemic situation, far from meeting the market demand.

Why did meltblown cloth have so little capacity in the past? Liu Feng said that in the past, although the national daily production capacity of 20 million masks, but not full-capacity operation, half of the production line is not open, mask demand is small, resulting in China's former melt-blown cloth manufacturers are also few.

It is difficult to expand the production of meltblown cloth, and it is also the bottleneck to limit the production capacity of meltblown cloth.

"The new production capacity needs a long cycle and a large investment, which can not catch up with the rapid increase in the production line of face masks in China in the near future, " the industry expert told Caijing, this is a big reason for the shortage of meltblown fabrics.

On March 3rd 002087.SZ  announced plans to invest 120m yuan in a six-month project to produce high-end melt-spun composite nonwovens. "The half-year construction cycle is already fairly fast, with two production lines, both domestic and foreign. " A company source pointed out that the meltblown cloth produced by the project can reach the BFE99 medical grade.

Liu Feng said that the raw material of meltblown cloth, polypropylene, is in sufficient supply and the price is stable. The neck is stuck in the production of meltblown cloth. The production line of meltblown cloth has a relatively large investment, with about 20 million imported complete sets of equipment and 300-600 million domestic equipment, and equipment delivery cycle and installation and commissioning cycle longer, "a production line without a three to five months down, " the enterprise does not dare to easily expand capacity.

Based on the investment of 200 million yuan by Sinopec, the cost of 10 meltblown fabric production lines is about 20 million yuan.

Also has the melt spurts the cloth enterprise to expand the production to have the doubt. "We hope that a meltblown cloth enterprise in the city will expand its production and give it subsidies for equipment procurement and preferential loan policies, " a local government official told CAIJING, but the company's intention to expand production is not very big, because of equipment procurement costs are too high.

The intermediate business layer changes hands, also in the melting spurts the cloth price to soar in played the role of fuel. "Some companies are hoarding or tightening resources because of concerns over raw material supplies, resulting in a phased shortage of meltblown cloth resources in the domestic market, " said the industry expert.

Liu Feng discloses, the price of melting spurt cloth is very confused now, it is middleman to hype more. He said that the melt-blown cloth currently circulating in the market is basically imported, and a small part of it is 'extruded' by someone using other relationships, "these 'unplanned' supplies flow into the hands of the middlemen who move several hands, who hoard the goods and then release them little by little. "

In the meltblown cloth collection wechat group, the reporter noted that some businesses are suspected of reselling meltblown cloth, in order to buy low sell high. But from within the group quoted prices, there is no less than 350,000 yuan per ton of supply, March 2 more meltblown cloth suppliers said that only change (mask) do not sell (meltblown cloth) , 445,000 yuan a ton do not sell. Based on the current wholesale price of 2.8 yuan for medical masks, the replacement price of 200,000 masks per ton of meltblown layout is equivalent to 560,000 / ton; based on the recent price of 3.5 yuan / ton for masks at Sinopec Gas stations, the replacement price for a ton of meltblown cloth is as high as 700,000 / ton.

"although the price is very high in the market now, I think it's all about settling accounts in the autumn, " Liu said. February 6, "two high" , the Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of Justice, "on the law to punish the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic crimes, " said the crime will be severely punished in accordance with the law to drive up prices.

"after March, the supply shortage in the meltblown cloth market will gradually ease, " said the industry expert. According to his understanding, after the Spring Festival, as the meltblown cloth market resources become tighter, some enterprises in China have urgently ordered the key equipment for the production of melt-blown cloth. It is expected that there are more than 100 melt-blown heads in order and production, and the new capacity will be more than 200 tons per day.

Among them, Sinopec is currently building 10 emergency melt-blown cloth production lines, the total production capacity of 18 tons per day. On March 4, Caijing learned that the main part of the two meltblown cloth production lines of Yan Mountains Petrochemical Company was about to be installed. The company's pricing of melt-blown cloth is still under discussion.

Policy subsidies help

The skyrocketing price of meltblown cloth not only makes the cost of the downstream mask factories increase greatly, but also makes the meltblown cloth manufacturers whose products are "requisitioned" by the government have some fluctuations in their hearts in the hope of making a certain profit. Under the circumstances of encouraging production expansion and balancing the interests of all parties, some local governments have introduced policies to support the meltblown fabric industry. Mask factory procurement of the product subsidies, to melt blown cloth enterprise series of preferential policies, bottom procurement, etc. , have appeared.

On February 17, the Putian Municipal Bureau of Industry and Information and the municipal development and Reform Commission jointly issued a paper focusing on supporting the procurement of key raw materials for the production of face masks: starting from February 15, the purchase of qualified meltblown cloth with a filtering rate of more than 95 percent shall be based on 120,000 yuan per ton, if purchases are made before 1 March, 90 per cent of the excess will be subsidized; if purchases are made before 1 April, 60 per cent of the excess will be subsidized.

Similarly, during the outbreak prevention and control period, Ningbo also provided a one-off incentive of $20,000 per ton to enterprises that purchased or distributed meltblown cloth outside the city. For enterprises that successfully developed meltblown cloth and were certified to meet the mask production requirements, a ONE-TIME GRANT OF $300,000.

As the core raw material of face mask, meltblown cloth has become the strategic material of epidemic situation and is controlled by the government.

"All the meltblown fabrics we produce are expropriated by the government. The price is definitely different from outside, but the government will give some subsidies, " a Shanghai meltblown fabric producer told Caijing, for example, the cost of labor, machinery and equipment, there is a certain proportion of subsidies. "The government will definitely pay for the products, even if the profits are not high. "

It further noted that the government was careful in its selection of requisitions. "prior to the official requisition, the relevant authorities need to conduct a comprehensive assessment of the company, such as whether it is a core project or not. All of the more than 10 factories that have been requisitioned in Shanghai have been inspected. "

A number of reporters interviewed by the "Caijing" meltblown cloth factory personnel said that the product was requisitioned by the government, the local government will give a certain subsidy.

In addition, some local governments to key epidemic enterprises to give loans discount interest policies, will be part of the meltblown cloth manufacturers included in the list of key enterprises.

On February 4, the General Office of the People's Government of Shandong Province issued several opinions on responding to the epidemic of pneumonia in the COVID-19 and supporting the steady and healthy development of small and medium enterprises, for the new loans to enterprises in 2020, the central finance has already granted discount interest at the People's Bank of China's interest rate of 50 per cent for reloans; for the key enterprises identified by the provinces for the prevention and control of the epidemic, the provincial finance has granted discount interest at the People's Bank's interest rate of 50 per cent for reloans, the discount period shall not exceed 1 year.

Jinfu, Shandong, with a daily production of 15 tons of meltblown cloth, is located in Dongying City, Shandong Province. "The company is not only a key safeguard enterprise for the prevention and control of the epidemic in Shandong Province, but also a key safeguard enterprise for the prevention and control of the epidemic as determined by the state, " a company official told Caijing.

As the only enterprise producing medical meltblown cloth in Jiangxi Province, Jiangxi Tianfilter New Material Co. , Ltd. has two production lines, and the meltblown cloth produced by the company has been listed as the urgently needed medical materials for epidemic prevention and control in Jiangxi Province, the company was also recommended to be included in the epidemic prevention and control discount loan support list.

Other provinces have similar policies. Under the policy warm wind, some companies previously on the sidelines to speed up production, but also some meltblown cloth enterprises plan to expand production.

A will produce meltblown cloth manufacturers in Liaoning, told the "Caijing" reporter, the relevant equipment has just arrived, is now finishing the installation work. "I actually considered this business in 2018 and 2019, and it has nothing to do with the current epidemic, but just because there are relevant preferential policies, I have accelerated the implementation of this project, " he said.

On Feb. 6, the Government of the People's Republic of China issued policies and measures to support the production and operation of small and medium-sized enterprises in response to the epidemic of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection, for key materials production enterprises, one-time pre-tax deduction is allowed for the purchase of equipment for expansion of production capacity, and the increment of value-added tax is fully refunded.

"We currently have 1-1.5 tons of meltblown cloth production capacity per day, and the company's products have been requisitioned by the government, " a meltblown cloth manufacturer told Caijing that the company plans to expand production and expects to double its total production capacity.

In addition, a number of places have made it clear that the government will purchase epidemic prevention materials that meet the requirements from key material production enterprises for epidemic prevention and control as strategic material reserves.
